      Senior <strong>.NET Engineer</strong> with more than <strong
        >20 years of software engineering experience</strong
      > building, modernising, and supporting business-critical systems across
      financial services, enterprise platforms, Azure cloud services,
      integrations, and SaaS products.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-4 text-base-content/75 leading-relaxed">
      My recent work focuses on enterprise lending and collections platforms,
      public API integration, SQL Server, legacy VB6 to C# modernisation, and
      root-cause debugging across large, long-lived codebases. I am a methodical
      investigator who traces failures through code, configuration, data, and
      version history rather than patching symptoms. Alongside professional
      engineering work, I design, build, and operate a growing portfolio of SaaS
      products used by real browser users.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-4 text-base-content/75 leading-relaxed">
      Earlier roles add breadth across automotive dealer management, healthcare,
      e-payment, housing communications, document management, workflow systems,
      data transformation, insurance, compensation services, and manufacturing.
      I have also spent around eight years in development lead, technical lead,
      Scrum Master, and project management responsibilities, managing teams up
      to 17 people.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-4 text-base-content/75 leading-relaxed">
      I actively use agentic AI development as part of my engineering workflow:
      Claude Code, Model Context Protocol (MCP), PowerShell automation, custom
      skills and commands, hooks, context/memory engineering, prompt design,
      root-cause investigation, refactoring, QA, documentation, and faster
      feedback loops.
    </p>
  </section>

